{
  "stem": "1169.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The first, the closing of the Jewish stores.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Second, every Jew had to wear a yellow star.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Children also.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Men, women, children.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You had to go on the street, you wore a yellow star.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then they started to build a ghetto, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which we were in the center of the Jewish neighborhood, so we were in it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they built a concrete wall around our neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "A tremendous effort.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I saw them working day and night building this wall.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They would ask families who lived further away to move into the ghetto, and families who lived in the ghetto to share their apartments with other families.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] We really began to lose our freedom.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The constant flow of people that we were used in my house stopped.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was no more traffic, no more in or out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And each day became more repressive than the day before.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We-- One event I will always remember from those days, from those weeks before the deportation, was there was-- they brought in the Jews from the neighboring villages, and they put them-- locked them up in camps in our city.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And there was a woman there, a well known lady from a very special family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she was about to give birth.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And my dad arranged to get a bed, a special type of bed upon which a woman gives birth.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There was no place else to put it in but in the synagogue itself, in our shul.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And my father asked them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They still had some respect for a rabbi there, in a big city.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the authorities let this lady out for the duration of giving birth.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And she gave birth to a baby in front of the Holy Ark in our synagogue.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
